snippet.textDisplay: Am I the only one who was wondering what in the hell Rodgers was doing late in the third quarter, into and throughout most of the fourth quarter, in terms of clock management?  Down 34-7 very late in the third, there seemed to be little to no urgency.  Tick, tick, tick.  They should've gone into no-huddle hurry up to press the issue.  On the contrary, I saw Rodgers sauntering around, doing his trademark long count to try to draw the defense offside, milking the play clock down to near zero, all while the GAME CLOCK was going tick, tick, tick, tick...I'm sure that the Niners were absolutely delighted.  Yeah, Aaron, take as much time as you need.  Oh, want to try a draw play there or a little dump off that doesn't get you out of bounds?  We'll take that, too.
